				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The <strong>source</strong> address is what is written to $4014 times 256.
<br />The <strong>destination</strong> address in OAM is the value written to $2003. Since OAM is only 256 bytes, one byte is enough to specify any part of it. If the end of OAM is reached and there are still bytes to copy, the address wraps around and goes back to 0.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
